# Eval run outputs (kept locally for diff'ing against baselines, not tracked).
# Baselines themselves (.planning/eval/baselines/) ARE tracked so they can
# anchor sub-task gates across machines. The runs/ dir contains *.json
# outputs (gitignored) AND human-authored *.md files like issues.md
# (tracked) — the negation pattern below restores .md files.
.planning/eval/runs/*.json
!.planning/eval/runs/*.md

# V26.15 — internal pipeline / business / architecture docs.
# These contain implementation details (provider names, model ids,
# version history, business model math, deep architecture notes)
# that we don't want exposed in the public repo. They stay LOCAL
# for context across coding sessions but are not tracked.
# V28.0.ST4 — .claude/CLAUDE.md REMOVED from this list per user
# direction. Now tracked so multi-dev pulls keep context in sync.
# Repo visibility implication: implementation details are now in git
# history. If this becomes a concern, restore the .claude/CLAUDE.md
# entry below + git rm --cached.
STATUS.md
BUSINESS_MODEL.md
DEPLOYMENT.md
docs/v14/
